Patch Set 3: (4 inline comments)

To solve the config problem, I think you should write your own configuration option class. For these I really like the "multi = True" setting which lets you put the setting across multiple lines nicely. Something so that you can specify directories like

  glance_filesystem_datadir = <string path1>,<int priority1>
  glance_filesystem_datadir = <string path2>,<int priority2>
  ...

But I think we still need to find a different name for the config, to avoid breaking old configurations that happen to have commas in them.

Patch Set 6:

Hi mark,

I have added one more option "filesystem_store_datadirs" which allows adding multiple directories as shown below.
Example:
filesystem_store_datadirs = /var/glance/store
filesystem_store_datadirs = /var/glance/store1:100
filesystem_store_datadirs = /var/glance/store2:200

I have avoided using ‘,' as it can used in file names as you pointed out in your earlier comments.
It raises BadStoreConfiguration if none or both of "filesystem_store_datadir" or "filesystem_store_datadirs" options are specified in glance-api.conf

Patch Set 6:

Reformatting above comment
Hi Mark,

I have added one more option "filesystem_store_datadirs" which allows adding multiple directories as shown below.

Example: 
filesystem_store_datadirs = /var/glance/store
filesystem_store_datadirs = /var/glance/store1:100
filesystem_store_datadirs = /var/glance/store2:200

I have avoided using ',' as it can used in file names as you pointed out in your earlier comments. It raises BadStoreConfiguration if none or both of "filesystem_store_datadir" or "filesystem_store_datadirs" options are specified in glance-api.conf
